[[File:Bounty crate detail.png|left|150px]]
A '''bounty crate''' was an item that contained an assortment of supplies that are commonly used in [[player killing]] activities. In order to purchase it from the [[Bounty Hunter Shop]] for 7 [[Bounty Hunter]] points, players required a [[combat level]] of 50. In addition, [[Ironman Mode|ironmen]] must have had the requirements to obtain the item for themselves. If the crate rolled an item the player did not meet the requirements for, a lower-level item was rolled instead. Ironmen were also unable to obtain Mysterious Emblems from the crate. It is unknown how this affected the probabilities of rolling the other items.

Players could buy up to a maximum of five crates, and could purchase an additional five for every target killed in [[Bounty Hunter]].

